This course focuses on security issues associated with the development and use of ICTs, the resulting problem area of 'cyber security' and relevant legal issues.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course will address cross-border implications of development and uses of ICTs and the resulting security concerns. It will familiarize the students with international law applicable to cross-border cyber conflict and discuss national security and defence aspects of ICTs. The students will learn to understand how uses of ICTs affect international security and how to resolve relevant issues under international law and policy.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students will be able to critically analyse the legal implications of global trends in the development and uses of ICTs; know the main trends related to politically motivated cyber-attacks and their legal implications, including the applicability of the law of armed conflict, state responsibility, and countermeasures; be able to construct legal strategies for mitigation of political cyber risk and be able to legally evaluate ICT related threats to public safety, national security, and international peace and security.
